<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Prodigal" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Prodigal,</orth> 1) lavish, profuse: <bibl n="shak. ven 755" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 755</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 411" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 411</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.5.15" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.3.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 3, 103</bibl> (<emph>the P. Son;</emph> cf. <emph>the prodigious son,</emph> in Launce's language, <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 3, 4</bibl>). <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.256" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 256</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.4.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 4, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 36</bibl>. With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>p. of all dear grace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 9</bibl></cit>. Adverbially: <cit><quote>how p. the soul lends the tongue vows,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 116</bibl></cit>.<lb />Substantively: <cit><quote>the niggard p. that praised her so,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 79" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 79</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.6.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 6, 14</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.278" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 278</bibl>. <emph>the P.,</emph> the spendthrift of S. Luke ch. 15: <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.5.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 5, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.6.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 6, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.157" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 157</bibl>.
<lb />2) ample, abundant: <cit><quote>spend his p. wits,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.64" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what p. portion have I spent,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 41</bibl></cit>. <emph>with</emph> <cit><quote>oppression of their p. weight,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.31" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 4, 31</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. bits,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 174</bibl></cit>.
<pb n="906" />
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>